            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="praenomen" key="Gaius">
                     <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aio</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Novius">Novio</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Thallus">Thallo</name>
               </persName>
               <lb n="2"/>et <persName>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Novia">Noviae</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Euhodia">Euhodiae</name>
               </persName>
               <lb n="3"/>coniugi eius et
                   <lb n="4"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="praenomen" key="Gaius">
                     <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aio</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Novius">Novio</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Sabinianus">Sabiniano</name>
               </persName>
               <lb n="5"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Novia">Noviae</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Iusta">Iustae</name>
               </persName>,
                   <lb n="6"/> fil<hi rend="tall">i</hi>s eorum <expan><abbr>merentib</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan>,
                   <lb n="7"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="praenomen" key="Gaius">
                     <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Novius">Novius</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Onesimus">Onesimus</name>
               </persName> feci<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied>
               <lb n="8"/> et sibi, et libertis, <expan><abbr>libertabusq</abbr><ex>ue</ex></expan>
               <lb n="9"/>suis.
                </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>For Gaius Novius Thallus, and for Novia Euhodia, his wife, and for Gaius
               Novius Sabianus, Novia Justa, (and) their deserving children, Gaius Novius Onesimus
               made (this), and for himself, and for his freedmen and freedwomen.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Line 6, tall I in "filIs" serving as "ii."</p>
         </div>
